  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Rapid advances in Large Language Model (LLM) technologies are promising to transform various aspects of economic activities.",
    "Burgeoning research has explored how LLMs can affect the future of work and labor markets (Brynjolfsson et al. 2018; Eloundou et al. 2024), productivity and creativity (Boussioux et al. 2024; Brynjolfsson et al. 2025; Noy and Zhang 2023; Zhou and Lee 2024, Doshi and Houser 2024), and knowledge dissemination (Burtch et al. 2024; Horton 2023; Quinn and Gutt 2023).",
    "An intriguing gap in the literature is the lack of empirical investigation into LLM's impact on the collaborative innovation foot_0 ecosystems in the knowledge economy-environments where contributors collectively advance shared projects.",
    "Open-source software development exemplifies such collaborative innovation through transparent, non-guided problem-solving where diverse contributors advance shared projects (Lerner and Tirole 2002, Belenzon and Schankerman 2008).",
    "Whereas extant innovation typologies focus on product innovation in guided setting (Tushman and Anderson 1986; Henderson and Clark 1990),"
  ],
